ately continue to thrive in the second century of their business today she continues to lead the charge as president of supply chain and sustainability at ul by providing her business acumen and leadership skills to the fastest growing business at ul which includes environment information and insights and furniture divisions her divisions tackle today’s complex supply chain and sustainability challenges through sciencebacked technologyenabled advocacy and solutions prior to her current position greenstein was chief marketing and strategy officer as well as senior vice president and chief commercial officer at ul with the distinction of being the youngest elected officer in the history of the company before coming to ul greenstein was a consultant at arthur andersen and was named to crain’s chicago business’s  under  in  greenstein holds an mba from university of michigan with a bs in business administration from the university of illinois email print sign up newsletter weekly email updates twitterrt techonomy yatishrajawat on mark zuckerbergs plans to pivot facebook and what the company can do to catch up httpstcowwvjwr… about  hours ago by k yatish rajawatzuckerberg is changing—can facebook catch up  techonomy httpstcothmgwtnwu via techonomy localcircles about  hours ago by k yatish rajawatrt delawareglobal delaware drives blockchain innovation techonomy stevenehrlich andreatinianow httpstcoqkhkwkyq httpstcoh… about  day ago by michael marquardtrt techonomy the state of delaware is becoming a driving force of blockchain innovation find out how and why httpstcowkysuanmnx … about  day ago by andrea tinianowrt delawareglobal delaware drives blockchain innovation techonomy stevenehrlich andreatinianow httpstcoqkhkwkyq httpstcoh… about  day ago by steve ehrlichrt techonomy the state of delaware is becoming a driving force of blockchain innovation find out how and why httpstcowkysuanmnx … about  day ago by vgirishrt techonomy the state of delaware is becoming a driving f