kbased product safety testing firm underwriters laboratories inc she presides over the sales and business development activities for ul the nations preeminent safety certification and testing firm for everything from electric frying pans to fire alarms shes been a key architect of an overhaul of the centuryold nonprofit company to make it more entrepreneurial and less bureaucratic shes also been the catalyst for uls expansion overseas in recent years making the case that the public pressure for more safety standards and product testing in developing countries like china and india presents a big opportunity for ul to increase revenue and its global footprint  to  amthe best time for breakfast at the bagel colleagues say her opinions carry weight with other senior leaders because she gets results shes able to select a team and lead them and drive solutions says sajeev jesudas president of uls international operations a lot of leaders fall apart on implementation ms greenstein who was raised on a farm in central illinois and now lives in chicagos old town neighborhood maintains a travel schedule that regularly takes her to the headquarters of some of the worlds bestknown companies to shore up customer relationships when shes not on the road evenings at home are often spent conversing via email with managers in japan or china where its early in the morning and she gets to the office by  am to catch managers in europe before they leave for the day shes been very involved in the customer relationships says al scolnik vicepresident for testing services at the virginiabased national electrical manufacturers assn all the trouble issues stop at her desk theres been no shortage of those since ms greenstein a former consultant with andersen consulting arrived at ul in  after decades of having a near monopoly on testing work in the united states by the late s ul found itself facing several competitors that had sliced its marketshare to about  manufacturers had started taking products to lesserknown testing labs to avoid uls notoriously slow and costly testing process the companys revenue growth nearly came to a standstill by  for the first time in its history ul laid off employees eliminating about  of its us workforce by  ms greenstein was put in charge of realigning the labs into a single organization with separate business units for the companys major markets to solidify the change she imposed a standardized price list for testing work customer service representatives instead of engineers now handle price quotes the company says thats reduced the wait times to a couple of days from two weeks the goal is to generate quotes in  hours that means more globetrotting while ensuring that her visits to the bagel will be an oasis of personal time in what has become a houraday career there are no such things as holidays because if theres a us holiday its not a holiday in china she says the bagel serves breakfast all the time bob tita  next   by crain communications inc  under  master list featured profile todays crains get our daily roundup of important business news